Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteTieHiLo(25.10)                                      deleteTieHiLo(25.10)

Name
       deleteTieHiLo  -  Deletes  placed tie cells from the netlist and recon-
       nects the tie input pins back to 1'b1 and 1'b0

Syntax
           deleteTieHiLo

       [-help]

       [-cell
               <tieCellName>
              | "<listOfTieCellNames>"]

       [-prefix
               <prefixName>]

       Deletes placed tie cells from the netlist and reconnects the tie  input
       pins  back to 1'b1 and 1'b0. Use this command if there are existing tie
       cells in design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each deleteTieHiLo parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:  man deleteTieHiLo.

       -cell <tieCellName>|<"listOfTieCellNames">
              The <tieCellName> argument specifies the cell name to delete.

              The " <listOfTieCellNames> " argument specifies the list of cell
              names  to  be  deleted,  which  must  be surrounded by quotation
              marks.

              Note: The <tieCellName> and "<listOfTieCellNames>" arguments are
              mutually exclusive.

       -prefix <prefixName>
              Specifies the prefix of the instances to delete.

       Note: If you do not specify any parameters, the command uses the global
       cell names if they were set previously with the setTieHiLoMode command.

Example
              * The following command deletes  all  placed  tie-off  cell  in-
                stances with the prefix ABC:

                deleteTieHiLo -prefix ABC

              * The  following command deletes all placed tie-off cells named:
                TIEOFF:

                deleteTieHiLo -cell TIEOFF

Related Information
